📐 Chapter 10: Rotational Dynamics

This module focuses on the transition from translational to rotational mechanics, emphasizing the role of inertia, torque, and conservation laws in rigid body dynamics.

🎯 Learning Objectives

Moment of Inertia (I): Master the calculation for various geometries and apply the Parallel Axis Theorem.

Rotational Kinematics: Bridge linear displacement, velocity, and acceleration to their angular analogs ($\theta, \omega, \alpha$).

Torque & Dynamics: Solve systems using $\tau = I\alpha$.

Conservation of Angular Momentum (L): Analyze isolated systems and collisions.

Energy in Rotation: Calculate Rotational Kinetic Energy and analyze "Rolling without Slipping" scenarios.

